00:01:46.060 --> 00:01:51.840
Review of Genetics, our own ancient mitochondrial
systems might be causing degenerative disease

00:01:51.840 --> 00:01:53.130
and cancer!

00:01:53.130 --> 00:01:57.290
Which brings me back to the earlier point,
does EVERYTHING cause cancer?

00:01:57.290 --> 00:02:00.870
Breathing causes it, making energy from food
causes it, what about food?

00:02:00.870 --> 00:02:04.869
My mom would always try to cook her pork chops
with the little black crusty bits on the edges,

00:02:04.869 --> 00:02:09.310
because it was DELECTABLE, but she stopped
when she found out the charred bit causes

00:02:09.310 --> 00:02:10.310
cancer.

00:02:10.310 --> 00:02:14.170
According to the American Cancer Society,
some starchy foods cooked at a high-temperature

00:02:14.170 --> 00:02:19.560
will produce acrylamide, a chemical found
in paper, wastewater, adhesives and cigarettes.

00:02:19.560 --> 00:02:24.319
Frying bacon, or grilling and smoking meats
can expose food to polycyclic aromatic hydrocarbons,

00:02:24.319 --> 00:02:29.319
a chemical known to cause skin, liver, and
stomach cancer in lab animals.

00:02:29.319 --> 00:02:32.560
Fried foods have their own problems.

00:02:32.560 --> 00:02:37.130
In the end, no serious science recommends
forgoing cooked food, but moderating the amount

00:02:37.130 --> 00:02:40.849
of grilled and blackened food is going to
decrease your cancer risk.

00:02:40.849 --> 00:02:41.849
AIR.

00:02:41.849 --> 00:02:42.849
FOOD.

00:02:42.849 --> 00:02:46.780
AND YOUR OWN BODY MAKING THOSE TWO THINGS
INTO ENERGY ALL CAUSE CANCER.

00:02:46.780 --> 00:02:50.950
So, relax, exercise and pay attention to what
you're eating, but don't give yourself an

00:02:50.950 --> 00:02:52.260
